12/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The army is training 300 more soldiers who will become the third Bulgarian battalion to be sent to Iraq. Lieutenant General Zlatan Stoykov, commander of the service staff of the land forces, says the soldiers will kick off their language training in English and Arabic on Friday (12 March). Tactical training, which begins next week, will be led by Lieutenant Colonel Petko Marinov, the commander of the first Bulgarian battalion in Iraq. Deployment is expected by the end of the month. (BTA, BBC - 11/03/04)
